A 33-year-old man was stabbed to death, allegedly by his girlfriend, in Broederstroom near Hartbeespoort Dam outside Brits, North West police said on Sunday. A 27-year-old woman allegedly stabbed her boyfriend in the neck in the early hours of Saturday, Sergeant Kelebogile Moleko said. According to information received, the police reacted to a complaint of murder where they found a man s body lying on the ground with a stab wound on his neck. It is alleged that the suspect stabbed the victim with a knife after they had an argument. The man was certified dead at the scene. The woman was expected to appear in the Brits Magistrate s Court on Monday. In a separate incident in the North West province, two men were arrested for allegedly beating a man to death in Seweding near Mahikeng. The men, aged 42 and 56, were arrested on Friday, Brigadier Sabata Mokgwabone said. A woman stopped police driving along Bray Road in Seweding village on January 4 and told them that the owner of premises, which she pointed out to the police, and some members of the community had allegedly assaulted her son, he said. The police went to investigate and found a severely beaten man and his hands tied at the back inside the yard. The man was taken to Mahikeng Provincial Hospital but was certified dead on arrival. A case of murder was opened for investigation and the suspects were eventually arrested. Investigation into the matter continues. The two were expected to appear in the Molopo Magistrate s Court in Mmabatho on Monday, Mokgwabone said. African News Agency (ANA)